{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a4225c12-e9ec-4e2d-8df4-278623ef5cd2","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x removed the VSTest compatibility bridge by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK implicitly included `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`, so `vstest.console` could still discover and run tests. In 4.x, that bridge is no longer referenced — tests are only exposed through the new **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** protocol.\n\n**To fix your CI, either:**\n\n1. **Migrate away from vstest.console** — use `dotnet test` (SDK 9.0.200+ speaks the new protocol natively) or run the test executable directly.\n\n2. **Re-enable the bridge** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the recommended long-term path since the VSTest bridge is considered legacy.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d616c740-e2f2-4d7a-87e1-b7fc9d468def","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 and MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code question about their repository.\n\nLet me look at what's in their working directory first to understand the context, but this seems like a general knowledge question about MSTest SDK versioning.\n\nThe key change is that starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4 (or more specifically, the move to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default), the VSTest compatibility layer was eventually removed. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, even though Microsoft.Testing.Platform was introduced, VSTest bridge/compatibility was still included by default. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer is no longer included by default, meaning vstest.console can no longer discover or run tests unless you explicitly opt back in.\n\n\nThe difference comes down to the VSTest bridge: version 3.x shipped with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge` enabled by default to maintain backward compatibility, but 4.x dropped it, so tests only work through the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner via `dotnet test` or direct executable execution. To restore vstest.console support, users can either migrate to `dotnet test` with .NET SDK 9+ or re-enable the bridge with a project file property.","outputTokens":647,"requestId":"BC20:354872:22E7F8B:26D9E91:69FAAB72"},"id":"619c9bd0-4f2e-494e-a64c-bfaef95f8fea","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:46:23.987Z","parentId":"f8a7a3c0-40ca-4887-ad30-eadcf896b963"}
